Why Choose Us
Events by Dubsdread is Orlando’s premier catering and event services company, delivering Culinary Excellence served with Southern Charm. Our team’s diverse background and extensive experience mean that every aspect of your event is in expert hands. We collaborate closely with you to bring your dreams to life, ensuring a seamless and stress-free experience. From planning to execution, we are committed to excellence, making your special day truly unforgettable.
Our Team
Our team brings over a century of combined experience to ensure your wedding or event is nothing short of incredible. Meet the talented individuals whose expertise and dedication will make your special day unforgettable.
Carissa Llewellyn-Burns
Director of Operations
Carissa joined the company in 2013. A communications and journalism graduate of Shippensburg University, she moved from Pennsylvania to Florida for sunshine and job opportunities. She began her career with Dubsdread as a banquet server and has worked her way through every position in the office to learn each aspect of the operation and is proud to be part of the amazing team. When she is not at work, Carissa enjoys time with her husband, Tyler, her crazy kiddos Connor and Cameron and her fur child, Roxy.
Christiana Bullard
Banquet Sales Manager
An Orlando native and a UCF graduate, Christiana worked in advertising before joining Dubsdread in 2005. She found the hospitality industry far more entertaining and mentally stimulating. Christiana enjoys humorous clients, problem-solving, and working with great colleagues. When she is not at work, she enjoys watching UCF football, going to the gym and spending time with her three “kids:” her daughter, husband and dog.
David Osmola
Senior Wedding & Event Coordinator
David joined the Dubsdread team in 2008 and is our Senior Wedding and Event Coordinator. Before coming on board, he worked in customer service positions in the wedding and airline industries. David strives to make every bride’s dream a reality, allowing his attention to detail and customer service skills to shine through. When he is not at work, David enjoys spending time with his friends and his dog, Sweet Pea, and visiting family in Michigan.
Michelle Edmiston
Event Specialist/Sales Representative
Michelle joined the team in 2017 and wears many hats, managing the property at The Highland Manor being one of them.  She grew up working in a family friend’s restaurant and expanded that knowledge working at country clubs, event venues, hotels and stadiums. After nearly three decades, she still loves helping her client's vision become a reality. When Michelle is not planning an event, she spends time with her husband Jay, son Blake, two rescue dogs and her vast extended family.
Shanna Paris
Event Specialist/Sales Representative
Shanna has been at Dubsdread since 2017. An Event Management graduate of the University of Central Florida’s Rosen College of Hospitality, she began her career with local wedding and destination event management companies. Since 2000, Shanna has planned weddings and events throughout the Orlando area, helping planners worldwide execute their corporate gatherings. At Dubsdread, she can focus on her passion to help brides make their day unique and personal. Shanna enjoys time with her four favorite guys when she’s not at work: her dog Giggsy, her sons Liam and Alfie and her husband Josh.
Peighton Ballant
Event Specialist/Sales Representative
Peighton is a native of Orlando and joined Dubsdread in 2018. In 2021, she earned her Event Management degree at the University of Central Florida’s Rosen College of Hospitality. Before joining the events team, Peighton was a hostess at The Tap Room at Dubsdread. Peighton enjoys working with prospective brides to discover what they are most interested in bringing to their special day and how to make those ideas come to life. When not at work, she enjoys caring for Dexter, her cat-child, going to the beach, hanging out with friends, and being a UCF Knight football fan.
Roxy Llewellyn-Burns
EBanquet Operations Ambassador
Roxy joined the team in January 2015. A Pet Smart’s Elite Obedience School graduate, she parlayed her training into a unique and valued office position. Roxy’s favorite role is greeting guests and fulfilling her Events by Dubsdread ambassador duties. When not at work, Roxy enjoys playing fetch with her humans, licking her brothers, belly rubs, treats, being completely spoiled and days at the doggie spa.
Kristen Berry
Wedding & Event Coordinator
Kristen joined the Dubsdread team as a catering captain in 2021 before transitioning to a wedding and event coordinator. She graduated with a degree in the arts and found she preferred the people-oriented nature, pacing, and problem-solving that comes with working in the service industry. Kristen enjoys planning, facilitating, and contributing to creating joyous occasions. When she is not at work, she loves traveling, cooking, working on creative projects and hanging out with her two cats, Diana and Henry.

Event and Catering Services
Welcome to Central Florida’s premier events and catering company, where we bring your vision to life. Our team specializes in weddings, corporate events, and special celebrations, crafting tailored experiences with exquisite cuisine and exceptional Orlando venues. We offer premium catering services at our exclusive Orlando locations and top venues across Central Florida, including the Winter Park Event Center, Orlando Science Center, and Harry P. Leu Gardens, as a preferred partner. Additionally, we are at your service for in-home or business catering.
Inquire Today

Highlights of Events by Dubsdread:
Whether you’re planning an executive meeting for 20, a party for 100, or an Orlando wedding for 350 people, we promise to deliver Culinary Excellence served with Southern Charm that compliments the venue, the event, and you!

The Highland Manor
The Highland Manor
Grand historic vintage elegance and Southern charm come together to create the perfect backdrop for your special event at
The Highland Manor
, a premier
wedding venue near Orlando
. With beautiful panoramic views of rolling hills, ancient oak trees, and wide verandahs, this one-of-a-kind estate is a stunning setting for
Orlando weddings
, upscale parties, and corporate events.
The gracious interiors of this 110-year-old historic building are rich with polished wood, crystal flourishes, and vintage details that make every photo shine and every guest feel transported. Whether you’re planning an intimate ceremony or a large celebration, The Highland Manor provides an unforgettable canvas for your dream day.
Weddings
Our authentic, historic Apopka manor home offers a timeless setting for your love story. With a wide wrap-around porch, elegant metal roof, and antique details both inside and out, this charming
Orlando-area wedding venue
exudes grace, sophistication, and Southern hospitality.
Exclusively managed by Events by Dubsdread
, we bring award-winning food and service to every celebration. Couples seeking a truly unique
wedding venue in Orlando
appreciate the variety and versatility of our four distinct spaces:
The Crystal Ballroom
– ideal for glamorous receptions with sparkling ambiance
The Oak Room
– rich in warmth and character, perfect for smaller ceremonies or dinners
The Glass Verandah
– offering gorgeous natural light and scenic views
The Oak Bar
– a stylish space for cocktails and mingling
Whether you’re planning a micro wedding for 20 or a grand affair for up to 350 guests, we provide the flexibility to accommodate your vision. We offer indoor and outdoor
wedding venue
options, including our showstopping
110-year-old oak tree
, a beloved setting for outdoor ceremonies in the greater
Orlando wedding
scene.
Venue Rental Includes:
Tables, chairs, china, glassware, silverware, and standard house linens
Ceremony and reception timeframes of 5 hours (or 4 hours for reception-only events, with optional extensions)
Access to on-site bridal suite and get-ready rooms
Brunch, afternoon, and evening timeframes available
Flexible pricing with discounts based on season, day of the week, and time of day
Convenient on-site parking
Hilton Garden Inn directly next door for your guests’ lodging needs
Located just outside of
Orlando
in the heart of historic Apopka, The Highland Manor offers the perfect balance of elegance, accessibility, and tranquility, making it a top-rated
wedding venue near Orlando
for couples from all over Central Florida and beyond.
View Brochure
You Get More Than a Venue - We Are at Your Service
When you plan your wedding with
Events by Dubsdread
, you get more than a beautiful location—you get a team dedicated to making your special day flawless. Our expert Event Specialists guide you from start to finish, combining deep experience with heartfelt service to help make your
Orlando wedding
unforgettable.
From the moment you book, our team becomes a part of yours, helping with every detail, timeline, and transition. It’s this personalized touch that sets The Highland Manor apart from other
wedding venues in Orlando
.
At Your Service
Our coordinators are renowned for their service and hospitality, which you simply won’t find elsewhere. Whether you’re planning your ceremony under our grand oak or inside the Crystal Ballroom, we ensure everything flows effortlessly.
PRE-EVENT SERVICES:
Tasting for Four – curated to match your preferences and wedding style.
Ceremony and reception layout planning to maximize beauty and functionality.
Vendor coordination and guidance to help you choose the best in Orlando.
Optional planning sessions and a final 1–2-hour planning meeting.
Rehearsal coordination for on-site events.
DAY-OF SERVICES:
Vendor check-in and timeline management.
Full-day coordination and execution of your wedding schedule.
Floral distribution for family and wedding party.
Cake cutting coordination and timeline transitions.
Guest greeters and placement of favors, centerpieces, and place cards.
A personal butler for the wedding couple—because you deserve to be pampered.
Whether it’s your first planning meeting or your final farewell wave as newlyweds, we’re honored to support every moment of your big day.
Inquire Today
Parties & Events
Let's Celebrate
The Highland Manor isn’t just one of Central Florida’s most loved
wedding venues
—it’s also a top destination for private parties, milestone celebrations, and corporate gatherings near
Orlando
. Whether you’re planning a rehearsal dinner, retirement party, or holiday bash, our venue delivers memorable moments with elegance and ease.
From cozy rooms to wide-open event halls, we offer flexible layouts to match your vision, complete with award-winning cuisine and impeccable service. Our event team works closely with you to reflect your style and occasion, customizing every detail from seating to menus.
Popular Celebrations Include:
Rehearsal Dinners
Anniversary Parties
Baby & Bridal Showers
Holiday Parties
Corporate Luncheons and Appreciation Events
Product Launches, Lectures, and Leadership Retreats
Celebrations of Life
We offer seating setups for sit-down receptions, theater-style events, cocktail mingling, or a creative mix of styles, giving you endless flexibility in our beautiful indoor and outdoor spaces.
Inquire Today
Catering
Dining Together
Food is a centerpiece of every great event, and as one of the few full-service
Orlando wedding venues
with in-house catering, The Highland Manor proudly offers a menu that’s as memorable as the setting. We offer flexible dining styles, including plated meals, buffet-style feasts, and elegant hors d’oeuvres receptions.
Your menu is built around your tastes, cultural traditions, dietary needs, and budget. Our experienced chefs craft every dish with precision and flair, helping elevate your event experience beyond expectations.
Guest Favorites Include:
Boursin-stuffed chicken with herb crust
Filet mignon with mushroom merlot sauce
Maryland-style jumbo lump crab cakes
Parmesan-crusted fresh catch of the day
Handmade mushroom ravioli and other vegetarian/gluten-free options
Looking for a twist? Our themed stations are always a hit:
I-Do Barbecue Buffet
: brined chicken, smoked tri-tip, hush puppies, and candied bacon skewers
Build-Your-Own Brunch Buffet
: mimosa bars, omelet stations, and eggs Benedict
Fun Food Bars
: shrimp & grits, sliders, mini pancakes, mac & cheese, and even nitro popcorn
Sweet Extras
: s’mores stations, bottomless mimosas, cotton candy bubbly bars, and late-night treats
With so many options and professional culinary guidance, your guests will be raving long after the last bite.
